<P> On that basis, at least 23 years would have elapsed between the start of
detailed site investigations at Sellafield in 1989 and first waste emplacement
in a deep repository there.  Sixteen of those years would have been devoted to
activities preceding the grant of planning permission for repository
development.
</P>
<P>4.4 As stated in paragraph 1.11 of <I>Nirex Report 327</I> of October 1992
[COR/504] and in paragraphs <A HREF="nrx12.htm#Para9.17">9.17</A> and 9.21 of
<B>PE/NRX/12</B>, all planning dates are conditional and subject in particular
to the progress of the scientific investigations at Sellafield and to the
availability of various consents. Nirex will not be declaring a new target date
for first waste emplacement until the Secretary of State's decision on the
current appeal is known.
</P>
