specifically to Sellafield.  (Boreholes and the RCF are components of spending
falling entirely within that category; percentage allocations have been applied
where appropriate to other components of spending.)  The table also shows
estimates of the spending which is generic, because it covers work which would
be done on the same basis wherever the Company's investigations were focused. 
(Much work on waste forms and cement technology, for example, is in the latter
category, as is the development of safety modelling techniques.)
</P>
